_:N6822075b61ea47deae1a7c6facf91193 <http://schema.org/description> "<p>Simon Hughes is GDF Executive Director at Nuclear Waste Services (NWS), with over thirty years’ experience leading and regulating infrastructure across the nuclear, water and environment sectors.</p>\n\n<p>Formerly NWS Director of Community Engagement and Siting, he has been accountable since 2020 for the UK’s GDF siting programme, integrating delivery with stakeholder engagement and policy alignment.</p>\n\n<p>He established NWS’ Major Permissions capability, shaping DCO and environmental permitting strategies and awarding a £78 million delivery partner framework to support investigations and construction readiness.</p>\n\n<p>His background spans private sector delivery and public regulation, including senior leadership at the Environment Agency, programme leadership at Thames Water and directing planning and consenting for Havant Thicket Reservoir.</p>\n" .
